node.accessibility_caption: Image may contain: text that says 'bentbutnotbreaking @ BENT BUT NOT BREAKING Empathy without boundaries is self destruction'

node.text:
I call one of my best friends “the boundary queen” because she is always saying to me that I need to put in better boundaries, to the point where I don’t even need to speak to her in some situations because I know it will just be “boundaries” haha. But she’s right. 
I have a lot of empathy and compassion but for a long time I have put other people first even if it’s destroyed me. It’s hard when I have strong values about helping people and being kind. But people use it and I often get very hurt. And this quote just sums it up perfectly. 
To my friend - I know I roll my eyes anytime the “B word” comes up 😂 but it’s helped me make progress and I appreciate you and your wiseness more than you know 😘
.
.
.
.

Posted @withrepost • @bentbutnotbreaking - Note to empaths: Having empathy is a wonderful trait to have. Being able to truly put yourself in someone else’s shoes is a true gift that enables you to support others in a way that not many could. However, boundaries for empaths are vital for your own healing.
